  <summary>03/11/1997--Introduced.
Amends the Federal Election Campaign Act of 1971 to prohibit any person from expending any funds for the purpose of influencing any campaign for election for Federal office unless the funds are subject to the limitations, prohibitions, and reporting requirements applicable to contributions and expenditures of such Act.</summary>
